pkgc:ID_1598662344 a skos:Concept ;
    dc:date "2023-04-17"^^xsd:date ;
    skos:prefLabel """Enterprises need to stop thinking about data as separate business aligned systems, and instead as a connected whole. Knowledge Graph technologies are one of the keys for connecting all of the enterprise into a unified data layer.

Graphs capture the fundamentally messy nature of data and provide a universal way of representing other data structures and connecting them together instead of replacing them, which would be invaluable for receiving, storing and modifying metadata from third parties, publishers and Scribd's own in-house Machine Learning teams.

This kind of zero to one thinking about data, and strong product execution skills will help me from day one to understand what data products best serve our customers, build out resilient systems, and bring this altogether into a roadmap of improvements that continue delivering Scribd's value of becoming an everyday part of reader's lives.""" ;
    pkg:sourceMap "new product Development Professional.mm" .

